lastic part of the\noptical conductivity. If such scaling extends to the low-frequency limit, a\nstrange metal relaxation rate can be estimated, and may ultimately be used to\ntest whether strange metals relax in a Planckian manner.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 May 2022 14:15:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 1 Jan 2023 17:54:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-03"}
